mode — kubeconform exits non-zero for malformed YAML regardless of schema availability or -ignore-missing-schemas flag\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- R-008 is fully resolved: kubeconform fixtures use -ignore-missing-schemas + YAML parse errors for deterministic offline behavior\n- R-011 is fully resolved: shadow directory approach preserves all co-located binaries\n- kubeval fixtures still show SKIP when kubeval is not installed — this is expected behavior\n- The KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS knob is a legitimate user-facing feature for CRD-heavy repos, not just a test hack\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":265,"cache_read_input_tokens":54744,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":265},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85fc0a59-c739-40c4-adb1-d8ca4c9716cd","uuid":"e4b11dbd-b680-4f36-9326-d2567cb4f55f"}
